tnam veteran's trauma, which often stems from his aggression rather than his victimization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aRape as a weapon of warzVietnamxHistoryy20th century. 0aRape victimszVietnam. 0aRape. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xAtrocities. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Critique. 4aGender and Sexuality : Feminist. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aSociology : Violence. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438430003423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438430003/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles